  "market_context": "After a prior bearish sweep, bias reversed bullish. Price moved from internal range liquidity (FVG) toward external range liquidity (previous swing high). Occurred during NY session (11:15–12:00 EST) on Sep 25, 2023.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept a 5-minute low (14880), formed an up-close candle, then on the 30-second chart revealed a bullish FVG as entry zone targeting the prior high for 1.83R.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified bullish bias after prior external-to-internal liquidity move and sought internal-to-external liquidity progression.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to 5-minute chart and observed a sweep of the 14880 level (low wick piercing 14880, closing above), confirming liquidity grab.",
    "Step 3: Noted the subsequent up-close candle on 5-minute, signaling potential bullish continuation and prompting descent to 30-second timeframe.",
    "Step 4: On 30-second chart, identified a bullish Fair Value Gap (FVG) as the entry zone, with stop placed below the FVG low (12-point stop).",
    "Step 5: Set target at the previous swing high (external liquidity), calculating 1.83R reward versus 1:1 fixed alternative."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade achieved ~1.83R by reaching the previous high; analyst explicitly stated this outcome in seg_005.",
  "lessons": "Internal liquidity (FVG) often serves as high-probability entry when price transitions toward external liquidity (swing high/low); aligning HTF bias with LTF FVG entries yields superior R:R.",
